Escape backticks in help messages for zsh

commit.message:
Escape backticks in help messages for zsh

As is, putting backticks in the short help of a command will cause zsh
to actually run that command when tab completing. This escapes those
properly so that the backtick literals are printed.

Don't call compinit in Zsh completion code

commit.message:
Don't call compinit in Zsh completion code

compinit resets the shell completion machinery, nuking any other dynamically added completions. It should be up to the user to call it once during his shell initialization.
